,Recommended,295850,11385091,"Posted: 23 July, 2014",all,Woodthorn,"""Vlad is an interactive graphic-novel with RPG elements where your decisions shape the outcome of your story. Each playthrough offers a different experience and immersive story totalling two hours of content.""This is entirely true. The story that the novel tells is quite short: In 80 minutes I have been able to make one playthrough each with the three classes available and there's still room for more runs.The game offers little in the way of instructions and throws you to the hub-screen immediately. The story progresses by selecting one of the locations (starting with Port, Square, and Bazaar, with Catacombs and Basilica added in a later chapter, and Palace last of all) and then deciding how to proceed in the provided scenario. Your choices alter your stats and might have some influence on later scenarios. After finishing three scenarios the story advances to the next chapter, with the climax after the 15th scenario. The stats aren't used until the very end of the climax when you encounter the Great Evil.All in all I found the game and its story to be interesting. Even though its fairly short I find the possibilties for several playthroughs to make it worthy of the 9.99 euro pricetag."
