76561197991088969,Recommended,295850,11281005,"Posted: 16 July, 2014",all,Sethfcm,"It definitely is a CYOA, and having beaten it is quite fun. The intro is abit...difficult as you first stumble to figure out it's style, but in the end I definitely enjoyed it, and found the final fight to be interesting as well.If it was longer or had more fights like that it'd be a definitely amazing game, as it is it's quite good a solid 8/10 or 7/10 if you're less action orientated.to expand on my review, the final fight is very difficult, and descriptive and indeed quite rewarding, but unfortunately very easy to lose so becareful. For it's price this game is definitely not a regretful purchase for me as 8.69 got me at least another 8 hours of entertainment so it's definitely better than renting a movie, and ontop of that It's a rare sort of adventure so it's particularly savorable.What is so rare about it? well it's dark, and grim, and definitely european, yet most of the gameplay takes place within the middle east and it shows as the people, and events reflect the location, yet also the characters identity. This is the sort of story you rarely read or see especially in a video game most especially in a choose your own adventure so for those whom enjoy Middle Eastern set games it's particularly nice, and for those whom enjoy dark, grim or even eldritch/lovecraftian settings it definitely will have some appeal.Still realize there is only one true fight with others being merely one decision or so, and it is rather short for each playthrough being roughly 1-2 hours of gameplay depending on reading speed, and choices. Prepare to lose the first play through as well.So TLDR, CYOA gameplay, only one 'real fight' and roughly 1-2 hour playthroughs a total of 6-12 hours to get 100% completion, and an interesting less often used arabic setting combined with a european horror/adventure theme it meshes well. Is it worth the money? perhaps so, perhaps not, and finally I rate it 7-8 out of 10.Edit: The only thing I truly wish to critique is both it's shortness, and the fact that there are areas which easily could have had more, such as the later journey, and connecting events between choices (choosing where to go) to reflect what you did the game isn't put together well, but has great quality."
