,Recommended,295850,29487657,Posted: 25 January,all,Aerie ( 絶望 ),"You know.. Looking back on it, it really is one of my favourite games, its just a shame it doesn't have a continuous replayability value but games based on text and story are often like that anyway.The main story is nice, but it is the side stories the game is littered with that makes it so fun. In each ""Chapter"" There are a few areas you can go to, the further you progress in the story, the more areas are unlocked. You can visit the same area more than once and it'll often give a new story or areas unlocked by previous chapters, but you can only visit so many. There are far too many areas and 'stories' that you'll never manage to visit them all in one game.. Or two.. Or three, let alone all the individual choices, but if you want to set aside a day just to do that, its definitely worth it for their enthralling tales and unusual, wonderful descriptions.Truthfully, its not got the best gameplay mechanics, but if you want to go into it and make the most of it, treat it as one of those Choose Your Own Adventure books you read as a kid rather than anything else, because thats what it is, a book, a pretty book of many tales with a beautiful art style and wonderously inspired connections to real world history and myths. Its Romanian, its gothy, its strange, thought provoking, mysterious and its written ♥♥♥♥ing perfectly, as far as games go, I love it to pieces and I'll keep it my mind.Theres quite simply nothing like it.. I honestly wish for more."
